    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:b47fbb51-40a7-52c6-bf97-a04a6de51aa5",
      "@type": [
        "legalproc:ChargingInstrument",
        "uco-core:UcoObject"
      ],
      "uco-core:name": "Second Superseding Indictment (Doc 66, filed 2025-09-18)",
      "uco-core:description": "Six-count grand jury indictment against Lindell, Maez-Schaack, Altenor, and Lauinger, signed by the foreperson and Acting U.S. Attorney Jennifer Klemetsrud Puhl. Source: PACER Doc 66 (indictment2), caption and true bill",
      "legalproc:instrumentType": "superseding-indictment",
      "uco-core:objectCreatedTime": {
        "@type": "xsd:dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-09-18T00:00:00-05:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:8dfa6e4d-df5c-5a42-a374-114b89e468fd",
      "@type": "uco-core:Relationship",
      "uco-core:source": [
        {
          "@id": "urn:uuid:b47fbb51-40a7-52c6-bf97-a04a6de51aa5"
        }
      ],
      "uco-core:target": [
        {
          "@id": "urn:uuid:750c1a57-9ed6-5713-b5b4-dce1033d0488"
        }
      ],
      "uco-core:kindOfRelationship": "Derived_From",
      "uco-core:isDirectional": {
        "@type": "xsd:boolean",
        "@value": "true"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:ee3f6d72-44cc-50c9-9d44-8590c0ce6e58",
      "@type": [
        "legalproc:CriminalCharge",
        "uco-core:UcoObject"
      ],
      "uco-core:name": "Count 1: Kidnapping",
      "uco-core:description": "On or about March 5 and 6, 2024, all four defendants, individually and by aiding and abetting, kidnapped, abducted, carried away, seized, confined, and held Victim A for some purpose or benefit without his consent, using telecommunication devices \u2014 a means, facility, and instrumentality of interstate and foreign commerce \u2014 in committing or in furtherance of the offense. Disposition shown is Maez-Schaack's guilty plea; the docket for the remaining defendants is not among the reviewed documents. Source: PACER Doc 66 (indictment2), Count 1",
      "legalproc:statuteCitation": "18 U.S.C. \u00a7\u00a7 1201(a)(1) & 2",
      "legalproc:countNumber": {
        "@type": "xsd:nonNegativeInteger",
        "@value": "1"
      },
      "legalproc:countLabel": "Count 1",
      "legalproc:offenseForm": "substantive",
      "legalproc:chargeDisposition": "convicted-by-plea",
      "legalproc:assertedIn": {
        "@id": "urn:uuid:b47fbb51-40a7-52c6-bf97-a04a6de51aa5"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:53ee2429-c2f5-5d09-8d8a-0afe71d741f9",
      "@type": [
        "legalproc:CriminalCharge",
        "uco-core:UcoObject"
      ],
      "uco-core:name": "Count 2: Conspiracy to Possess with Intent to Distribute and Distribute a Controlled Substance",
      "uco-core:description": "From late February 2024 through early April 2024, Lindell, Maez-Schaack, and Altenor conspired to possess with intent to distribute and distribute a methamphetamine mixture (Schedule II). The grand jury specifically found 500 grams or more attributable to each (\u00a7 841(b)(1)(A)(viii)) and found Lindell's two prior serious-drug-felony convictions. Eleven overt acts include the $6,000 drug debt (at least 500 grams), Lindell ordering Maez-Schaack and Altenor to kidnap, assault, and rob Victim A to collect it, firearm possession, concealment, U.S. currency, mobile payment apps and social media, and cellular telephones. Source: PACER Doc 66 (indictment2), Count 2, drug quantity, prior convictions, overt acts 1-11",
      "legalproc:statuteCitation": "21 U.S.C. \u00a7\u00a7 846, 841(a)(1), 841(b)(1)(C), 841(b)(1)(A)(viii)",
      "legalproc:countNumber": {
        "@type": "xsd:nonNegativeInteger",
        "@value": "2"
      },
      "legalproc:countLabel": "Count 2",
      "legalproc:offenseForm": "conspiracy",
      "legalproc:chargeDisposition": "convicted-by-plea",
      "legalproc:assertedIn": {
        "@id": "urn:uuid:b47fbb51-40a7-52c6-bf97-a04a6de51aa5"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:3ef0af0c-9352-5047-a2e1-5bf2bd685eb2",
      "@type": [
        "legalproc:CriminalCharge",
        "uco-core:UcoObject"
      ],
      "uco-core:name": "Count 3: Interference with Commerce by Robbery (Hobbs Act)",
      "uco-core:description": "On or about March 5 and 6, 2024, Maez-Schaack and Altenor obstructed commerce by robbery, taking Victim A's Ford F-250 \u2014 a vehicle moving in interstate commerce \u2014 from his person and presence against his will by actual and threatened force, violence, and fear of injury. Dismissed as to Maez-Schaack on the government's motion at sentencing per the plea agreement. Source: PACER Doc 66 (indictment2), Count 3; Source: PACER Doc 128 (judgment), Sheet 1 dismissals",
      "legalproc:statuteCitation": "18 U.S.C. \u00a7\u00a7 1951 & 2",
      "legalproc:countNumber": {
        "@type": "xsd:nonNegativeInteger",
        "@value": "3"
      },
      "legalproc:countLabel": "Count 3",
      "legalproc:offenseForm": "substantive",
      "legalproc:chargeDisposition": "dismissed",
      "legalproc:assertedIn": {
        "@id": "urn:uuid:b47fbb51-40a7-52c6-bf97-a04a6de51aa5"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:e04b79d0-25fc-5765-a8f3-8efba323c729",
      "@type": [
        "legalproc:CriminalCharge",
        "uco-core:UcoObject"
      ],
      "uco-core:name": "Count 4: Brandishing a Firearm During and in Relation to a Crime of Violence",
      "uco-core:description": "On or about March 5 and 6, 2024, Maez-Schaack and Altenor knowingly brandished firearms during and in relation to a crime of violence, namely the Hobbs Act robbery charged in Count 3. Carries a mandatory minimum of 7 years consecutive to any other sentence. Source: PACER Doc 66 (indictment2), Count 4; Source: PACER Doc 101 (plea), para. 7 penalties",
      "legalproc:statuteCitation": "18 U.S.C. \u00a7\u00a7 924(c)(1)(A)(ii) & 2",
      "legalproc:countNumber": {
        "@type": "xsd:nonNegativeInteger",
        "@value": "4"
      },
      "legalproc:countLabel": "Count 4",
      "legalproc:offenseForm": "derivative",
      "legalproc:chargeDisposition": "convicted-by-plea",
      "legalproc:assertedIn": {
        "@id": "urn:uuid:b47fbb51-40a7-52c6-bf97-a04a6de51aa5"
      },
      "legalproc:objectOffense": {
        "@id": "urn:uuid:3ef0af0c-9352-5047-a2e1-5bf2bd685eb2"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:bee4760b-0a75-5b12-9876-dfeaf4c3094c",
      "@type": [
        "legalproc:CriminalCharge",
        "uco-core:UcoObject"
      ],
      "uco-core:name": "Count 5: Possession of a Firearm in Furtherance of a Drug Trafficking Crime",
      "uco-core:description": "On or about April 2, 2024, Maez-Schaack knowingly possessed a SIG Sauer, Model P365, 9mm pistol, bearing Serial Number 66F717834, in furtherance of the drug trafficking conspiracy charged in Count 2. Dismissed as to Maez-Schaack on the government's motion at sentencing per the plea agreement. Source: PACER Doc 66 (indictment2), Count 5; Source: PACER Doc 128 (judgment), Sheet 1 dismissals",
      "legalproc:statuteCitation": "18 U.S.C. \u00a7 924(c)(1)(A)",
      "legalproc:countNumber": {
        "@type": "xsd:nonNegativeInteger",
        "@value": "5"
      },
      "legalproc:countLabel": "Count 5",
      "legalproc:offenseForm": "derivative",
      "legalproc:chargeDisposition": "dismissed",
      "legalproc:assertedIn": {
        "@id": "urn:uuid:b47fbb51-40a7-52c6-bf97-a04a6de51aa5"
      },
      "legalproc:objectOffense": {
        "@id": "urn:uuid:53ee2429-c2f5-5d09-8d8a-0afe71d741f9"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:60dc63ea-df35-5a8d-b685-5721cc51aab1",
      "@type": [
        "legalproc:CriminalCharge",
        "uco-core:UcoObject"
      ],
      "uco-core:name": "Count 6: Possession of a Firearm by a Convicted Felon",
      "uco-core:description": "On or about April 2, 2024, Maez-Schaack, knowing he had nine prior North Dakota felony convictions (reckless endangerment x3, drug paraphernalia, fleeing x3, and controlled-substance possession, judgments entered 2018-12-07, 2020-11-02), knowingly possessed in and affecting commerce the SIG Sauer P365 pistol, Serial Number 66F717834. Source: PACER Doc 66 (indictment2), Count 6",
      "legalproc:statuteCitation": "18 U.S.C. \u00a7\u00a7 922(g)(1), 924(a)(8) & 2",
      "legalproc:countNumber": {
        "@type": "xsd:nonNegativeInteger",
        "@value": "6"
      },
      "legalproc:countLabel": "Count 6",
      "legalproc:offenseForm": "substantive",
      "legalproc:chargeDisposition": "convicted-by-plea",
      "legalproc:assertedIn": {
        "@id": "urn:uuid:b47fbb51-40a7-52c6-bf97-a04a6de51aa5"
      }
    },
